Remake of the blaxploitation thriller, starring Samuel L Jackson, Christian Bale and Toni Collette.(n)

programme.title: Hondo
programme.desc: A hard-boiled cavalry scout with a feral dog as companion stumbles across a woman and her child stranded on their homestead deep inside hostile territory. Despite repeated attacks by the Apaches, they refuse to leave their home, leaving the scout with no choice but to stay and defend her. Western, starring John Wayne, Geraldine Page, Ward Bond and Michael Pate.(n)

programme.title: Night Moves
programme.desc: A farmer, a high-school drop-out and an ex-soldier form a militant environmentalist group, and plot to blow up a controversial dam. While their plan is successful, it has many shocking consequences, and they are faced with a series of moral dilemmas in the aftermath. Thriller, starring Jesse Eisenberg, Dakota Fanning and Peter Sarsgaard.(n)

programme.title: A Fistful of Dollars
programme.desc: A mysterious gunslinger rides into a town on the Mexican border divided by two warring families. After killing the henchmen of one clan, he seems to have made it clear where his loyalties lie and is hired by their rivals. However, he is secretly planning to play them off against each other to his own advantage. Sergio Leone's Western, with Clint Eastwood making his first appearance as The Man with No Name alongside Gian Maria Volonte and Marianne Koch.(n)

programme.title: For a Few Dollars More
programme.desc: An enigmatic gunslinger forms an uneasy alliance with a military veteran to track down a notorious outlaw - but tensions simmer as their very different motives for the hunt put them increasingly at odds. Sergio Leone's Western sequel, starring Clint Eastwood, Lee Van Cleef, Gian Maria Volonte, Josef Egger, Mara Krup and Klaus Kinski.(n)

programme.title: The Good, the Bad and the Ugly
programme.desc: A laconic gunslinger, a ruthless hired killer and a conniving outlaw hunt for a cache of loot during the chaos of the American Civil War. However, each is privy to only part of the information necessary to find it, setting in motion a series of deadly betrayals. The third film in Sergio Leone's Spaghetti Western trilogy, starring Clint Eastwood as the Man with No Name, with Lee Van Cleef and Eli Wallach. With a soundtrack by Ennio Morricone.(n)

John Boorman's thriller based on James Dickey's novel, with Burt Reynolds, Jon Voight, Ronny Cox, Ned Beatty and Bill McKinney.(n)

programme.desc: The highly strung producer of a Washington news bureau falls for a handsome but arrogant and totally untalented new anchorman, but is unaware a humble reporter friend is deeply infatuated with her. Comedy, starring Holly Hunter, William Hurt and Albert Brooks. Featuring an uncredited cameo from Jack Nicholson.(n)

programme.title: Mississippi Burning
programme.desc: Two mismatched FBI agents, one a tough former sheriff, the other a by-the-book idealist, are sent to a small town in the Deep South to investigate the disappearance of three civil rights activists, only to come up against a conspiracy of silence. Alan Parker's drama set in the 1960s, starring Gene Hackman, Willem Dafoe, Brad Dourif, Michael Rooker, R Lee Ermey and Frances McDormand.(n)

programme.title: The Gunfighter
programme.desc: Gunslinger Jimmy Ringo looks forward to a life of domestic peace after being given a chance to settle down with his once estranged wife and their child. However, a young upstart with dreams of slaying a legend challenges Ringo to a gunfight but dies, setting his three vengeful brothers on the older man's trail. Western, starring Gregory Peck, Millard Mitchell, Karl Malden and Helen Westcott.(n)

programme.title: Retribution
programme.desc: A hard-drinking single father struggles to cope with raising two sons alone. One of the boys is consumed with anger, and seeks an outlet for his rage in the dangerous sport of motocross. As his reckless behaviour gets out of control, his troubled parent has to get through to him before the family is torn apart. Drama, starring Aaron Paul and Juliette Lewis.(n)

programme.title: The Diving Bell and the Butterfly
programme.desc: Biographical drama based on the life of magazine editor Jean-Dominique Bauby, who was left almost entirely paralysed by a stroke and could only move his left eyelid. By working out a code using blinking, he was able to dictate a book describing life in his condition, as well as his dreams, memories and fantasies. Starring Mathieu Amalric and Emmanuelle Seigner. In French.(n)

programme.title: World Trade Center
programme.desc: Fact-based drama inspired by the events of September 11. The film focuses on two police officers who were trapped in the wreckage of one of the Twin Towers while they oversaw the evacuation, and examines the effects of the tragic incident on their families. Directed by Oliver Stone and starring Nicolas Cage, Maria Bello, Michael Pena and Maggie Gyllenhaal.(n)

programme.title: A Place in the Sun
programme.desc: A wage-slave in his uncle's factory has big ambitions. Just as he comes close to marrying a wealthy socialite, a poor working-class girl with whom he had a brief, casual affair tells him she is pregnant with his child. When she threatens to disclose the truth, he makes a series of decisions which bring terrible consequences in their wake. Oscar-winning drama, starring Montgomery Clift, Shelley Winters, Elizabeth Taylor,and Raymond Burr.(n)

programme.title: The Ten Commandments
programme.desc: Egyptian prince Moses discovers his real roots are Hebrew after being banished from the land by his jealous half-brother. He returns from exile on a quest to free his people from enslavement by the new pharaoh, and warns of terrifying consequences if the ruler fails to let his people go. Cecil B DeMille's biblical epic, starring Charlton Heston, Yul Brynner, Edward G Robinson and Anne Baxter.(n)

programme.title: Oscars 2016 Nominations Special
programme.desc: Alex Zane looks at the nominees for this year's Academy Awards, as critics and film fans pick their favourites.(n)

programme.title: Juno
programme.desc: A teenage girl finds herself pregnant after a one-night stand with her best friend. Deciding to give her baby up for adoption, she thinks she has found the perfect parents in a yuppie couple. However, over the next nine months she begins to experience doubts about her plans. Comedy, starring Ellen Page, Michael Cera, Jennifer Garner and Jason Bateman.(n)

programme.title: I Origins
programme.desc: A biologist researching the evolution of eyes uncovers shocking evidence that suggests people are reincarnations of the dead - a fact that could have far-reaching consequences for the human race. Drama, starring Michael Pitt, Brit Marling and Archie Panjabi.(n)

programme.title: Fear and Loathing in Las Vegas
programme.desc: A reckless sports writer and his lawyer hit the highways in search of the American Dream, heading for the Nevada gambling capital in a convertible stocked with alcohol and drugs. Comedy, adapted by Terry Gilliam from Hunter S Thompson's book, starring Johnny Depp, Benicio Del Toro, Ellen Barkin, Christina Ricci and Tobey Maguire.(n)

programme.title: Breakfast
programme.desc: A round-up of national and international news, plus sports reports, weather forecasts and arts and entertainment features.(n)

programme.title: Match of the Day
programme.desc: Gary Lineker presents highlights of the latest Premier League matches, including Manchester City v Crystal Palace at the Etihad Stadium and Chelsea v Everton at Stamford Bridge, where the away sides were looking to secure rare wins on their travels over their opponents. Plus, action from Tottenham Hotspur v Sunderland, Bournemouth v Norwich City, Newcastle United v West Ham United, Southampton v West Bromwich Albion and Aston Villa v Leicester City.(n)

programme.title: The Andrew Marr Show
programme.desc: Round-up of the week's stories, featuring interviews with key figures in politics and current affairs, and leafing through the Sunday papers. Including news and weather at 9.00.(n)

programme.title: The Big Questions
programme.desc: Nicky Campbell presents the show live from Harris Academy, Peckham, discussing topics including misogyny on social media and whether it is possible for all religions to be right.(n)

programme.title: Sunday Politics London
programme.desc: The week's events at Westminster, presented by Andrew Neil. Including news and a regional round-up.(n)

programme.title: Bargain Hunt
programme.desc: Charlie Ross and Jonathan Pratt join two teams in the market town of Hungerford in Berkshire, as they go in search of affordable and potentially lucrative items. Presenter Tim Wonnacott visits the Vyne, a 16th-century country house in Basingstoke, Hampshire.(n)

programme.title: Homes Under the Hammer
programme.desc: Lucy Alexander and Martin Roberts explore a development in the Highlands village of Kyle of Lochalsh, a property with a converted stable block in Kent and a mid-terrace house in Liverpool, before finding out what they fetched at auction.(n)

programme.title: Eat Well for Less
programme.desc: At a time when food prices are soaring, MasterChef host Gregg Wallace and grocer Chris Bavin set out to get to the bottom of a key culinary debate - when should shoppers spend more and when should they spend less? The hosts take on a classic British dish, fish and chips, and while Gregg claims splashing out that little bit extra makes all the difference when it comes to taste, Chris argues he can deliver the same meal on the cheap. Along the way, they explode popular myths and ask key questions about food production, and the programme ends with a feast where members of the public give their verdicts on the dishes in a blind-taste test. Who will come out on top?.(n)

programme.title: Escape to the Country
programme.desc: Highlights of the series from house-hunts in Somerset. Johnnie Irwin learns how to make Cheddar cheese and Jules Hudson checks out sand sculptures in Weston-Super-Mare.(n)

programme.title: Lifeline
programme.desc: Broadcaster Anneka Rice appeals on behalf of Riding for the Disabled, a charity dedicated to making a lasting difference to people with physical and learning disabilities through horse riding.(n)

programme.title: Songs of Praise
programme.desc: John Craven visits Cumbria to meet local people helping with the clean-up after the recent devastating floods and visit a water damaged church that has become a relief centre.(n)

programme.title: Great Barrier Reef with David Attenborough
programme.desc: The naturalist examines what the next few decades may hold for this remarkable ecosystem, and looks at the work of scientists who are trying to preserve the area and the species that inhabit it, assisted by research vessel the Alucia. He also embarks on an ambitious attempt to dive further into the reef than ever before to witness the resilient coral that live down in the depths and see if they hold answers that may help to overcome challenges that lie ahead, as the impact of humans on the reef continues to take its toll. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: Countryfile
programme.desc: Matt Baker and Ellie Harrison explore Gloucestershire, visiting Batsford Arboretum, where the trees are being given a health check, and the International Centre for Birds of Prey, where Californian Condors are being bred in captivity. Plus, Josh Widdicombe visits a Welsh campsite and beach that holds special memories for him and his family, Adam Henson meets one of the finalist from last year's Food and Farming Awards and Tom Heap reports on neglected and abandoned horses. Including Weather for the Week Ahead.(n)

programme.title: Still Open All Hours

However, the reluctant groom has cold feet, and it falls to the miserly shopkeeper to ensure he makes it to the church on time. The marital atmosphere also has a marked effect on Mrs Featherstone, who steps up her search for a fourth husband - with Granville and Mr Newbold finding themselves likely candidates to be the next lucky man.(n)

Her husband struggles to cope with his daughter's needs, but the sisters rally round to support the family. Trixie teaches a keep fit class which results in a medical emergency, leaving her determined to teach her patients to understand their own bodies.(n)

programme.title: War & Peace
programme.desc: Pierre fights a duel with Dolokhov, and the outcome inspires him to make changes in his life. Helene re-enters high society and pursues a new relationship, while Andrei is consumed with guilt and seeks seclusion in a country house he has built. The count tries to keep his spending under control, while Natasha and Sonya both receive unexpected marriage proposals. Nikolai makes the mistake of placing his trust in a dangerous friend, and a treaty between Russia and France leaves the future looking uncertain.(n)

Drama, starring Dominic Cooper, Ludivine Sagnier and Philip Quast.(n)

programme.title: Breakfast

programme.title: Wanted Down Under
programme.desc: An Australian hopes to persuade her husband to move to her native country, with the pair spending a week in Perth to see how he takes to life Down Under. Nicki Chapman presents.(n)

programme.desc: It is the first day at work for the new practice manager Anthony, while Mrs Tembe has to return to reception. Ayesha gets drawn into something unsavoury when she goes back to her old address to collect some post.(n)

programme.desc: The priest investigates the disappearance of a parishioner who believed she was being haunted by her sister, who went missing years before. Mark Williams stars in the 1950s-set crime drama based on the stories by GK Chesterton, with Sorcha Cusack, Hugo Speer and Tom Chambers.(n)

programme.title: For What It's Worth

Presented by Alexander Armstrong and Richard Osman.(n)

programme.title: The One Show

Martin turns to Sonia for help after finding a dishevelled Stacey on the Square, while Mo tells Kat she is not welcome at Charlie's funeral. Mick and Linda extend their honeymoon, so Babe suggests Nancy should take over the running of the Vic from Shirley.(n)

Fergus Walsh gains access to patients who have agreed to take part in a pioneering trial in which a crossover cancer treatment appears to have enabled some MS sufferers to regain their movement.(n)

programme.desc: Part one of two. An ex-convict is found murdered in his home and suspicion immediately lands on a recently released child killer. Nikki and the Lyell team are introduced to forensic psychologist Sasha Blackburn, who works closely with those released from prison on licence, as both the victim and one of the suspects are clients of hers. The investigators soon learn that it is not just the minds of these young men that are fragile, but their freedom is too. Forensic crime drama, guest starring Lyndsey Marshal and Niamh Cusack.(n)

programme.title: Tracey Ullman's Show
programme.desc: The Duchess of Cornwall babysits Prince George for the day, Dame Judi Dench causes trouble in a five-star hotel and a Midlands couple return from holiday to find an illegal immigrant hidden under their motorhome. Plus, the tutor of a silver surfers computer class offers some extraordinary tips, and Angela Merkel entertains embassy staff with a song. Comedy sketch show, guest starring Steve Pemberton.(n)

programme.title: The Graham Norton Show
programme.desc: Matthew Perry talks about his forthcoming West End playwriting debut - The End of Longing - in which he also stars, while Gemma Arterton discusses her role as the 17th-century royal mistress in Nell Gwynn, due to open at London's Apollo Theatre next month. Actress Miriam Margolyes talks about new documentary series The Real Marigold Hotel and there's music from Jack Savoretti who performs catapult. The host also subjects more audience members to the dreaded red chair - so their stories had better be good.(n)

programme.title: This Is BBC Two

programme.title: Countryfile
programme.desc: Matt Baker learns about oilseed-rape farming in Hertfordshire and helps chef Jean-Christophe Novelli whip up a feast using the healthy product. Ellie Harrison goes in search of wildlife in Heartwood Forest, chef Tony Singh visits Loch Awe in the Western Isles, Tom Heap reports on cuts to rural public transport and Adam Henson meets the winner of last year's Countryfile Farming Hero award before announcing this year's nominees.(n)

programme.title: Saturday Kitchen Best Bites
programme.desc: James Martin presents highlights of the series, recalling his favourite moments from previous years in the kitchen.(n)

programme.title: James Martin: Home Comforts
programme.desc: The chef is joined by racing driver Jason Plato as he uses clever cooking techniques to serve up dishes that look lavish but will not cost an arm and a leg.(n)

programme.title: James Martin: Home Comforts
programme.desc: Italian chef, restaurateur and food expert Antonio Carluccio joins the presenter as he makes a boozy pudding that reminds him of French holidays and a tasty recipe he netted on a recent fishing trip.(n)

programme.title: MOTD2 Extra
programme.desc: Mark Chapman presents football discussion with the Match of the Day team, focusing on the headlines from yesterday's matches and news ahead of today's fixtures.(n)

programme.title: Live Snooker: The Masters
programme.desc: Hazel Irvine presents coverage of the opening eight frames of the final from Alexandra Palace, London, where the best-of-19-frames match takes place. Neil Robertson faced Shaun Murphy in the showpiece match 12 months ago, but lost the first five frames as the Magician demonstrated his brilliant best. With commentary by Dennis Taylor, Ken Doherty, Stephen Hendry, John Virgo, Steve Davis and John Parrott. Subsequent programmes subject to change.(n)

programme.title: Ski Sunday
programme.desc: Graham Bell and Ed Leigh present highlights of the men's World Cup downhill race from Wengen in Switzerland, and the women's giant slalom from the German resort of Ofterschwang. Plus, behind the scenes of Legs of Steel, the spectacular free-skiing film.(n)

programme.title: World's Sneakiest Animals
programme.desc: Chris Packham features animals that utilise devious tactics to win a mate and raise a family, such as bower birds and fiddler crabs, who use optical illusions to impress a female, and male topi antelope, who fake danger to give them an edge. He also looks at family life, including the chicks that blackmail their parents, and the honeyguide bird that dupes another species into raising its young. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: Live Snooker: The Masters
programme.desc: Hazel Irvine presents concluding coverage of the final from Alexandra Palace, London, where a maximum of 11 frames will be played to decide this year's champion. Shaun Murphy claimed his first Masters title with a 10-2 victory over Neil Robertson in 2015, winning all four frames in the second session to avenge a defeat suffered at the hands of `the Thunder' in this match three years earlier. With commentary by Dennis Taylor, Ken Doherty, Stephen Hendry, John Virgo, Steve Davis and John Parrott. Subsequent programmes subject to change.(n)

programme.title: Jo Nesbo's Headhunters
programme.desc: A corporate headhunter funds his glamorous lifestyle with a sideline in fine-art theft. When he meets a former mercenary in possession of a valuable painting, he cannot resist trying to steal it - but the robbery leads him to uncover a secret that threatens to cost him everything. Crime thriller, starring Aksel Hennie and Nikolaj Coster-Waldau. In Norwegian, Danish, Russian and English.(n)

programme.title: Countryfile
programme.desc: Matt Baker learns about oilseed-rape farming in Hertfordshire and helps chef Jean-Christophe Novelli whip up a feast using the healthy product. Ellie Harrison goes in search of wildlife in Heartwood Forest, chef Tony Singh visits Loch Awe in the Western Isles, Tom Heap reports on cuts to rural public transport and Adam Henson meets the winner of last year's Countryfile Farming Hero award before announcing this year's nominees.(n)

programme.desc: Essie allows her personal life to affect her work when she has to deal with a case involving an adopted son donating his kidney to his birth mother. Guy's career goes from strength to strength, but at a cost, while Morven suggests to Arthur that they keep their new relationship a secret, although things don't quite go to plan.(n)

programme.title: This Is BBC Two
programme.desc: Preview of upcoming programmes from BBC Two.(n)

programme.title: Rip Off Britain: Holidays
programme.desc: Angela Rippon, Gloria Hunniford and Julia Somerville reveal how scammers have taken advantage of a company that has revolutionised the way millions of people now travel. Plus, how to contend with the problem of overbooked holidays.(n)

programme.title: Wanted Down Under
programme.desc: Determined to give his two children their best life possible Charlie Bennett, believes that emigrating to Australia could be the answer. However, son Max is worried about leaving his friends behind and wife Stephanie realises such a move could mean saying goodbye to her grandparents for the last time. Nicki Chapman watches on to see if a trial week in Queensland lives up to their expectations.(n)

programme.title: Close Calls: On Camera
programme.desc: Footage of near misses caught on CCTV, featuring a delivery van smashing into a couple's home and trapping them in their bedroom and the water ski jumper who got it wrong at take off and hit the water at 70mph. Presented by Alex Jones.(n)

programme.title: World's Sneakiest Animals
programme.desc: Chris Packham features a host of animals that use deceptive tactics to find food. Some trick their prey, like the manipulative mantis which looks like a flower and killer whales which set traps using sound. Others cheat each other - sea otters demand ransoms after kidnapping each other's pups - and some, like African bird the drongo and monkeys, fool other species. In parks, meanwhile, grey squirrels are at war in stealing raids and it seems these animal liars, cheats and hustlers really will stop at nothing to get a meal.(n)

programme.title: Victoria Derbyshire
programme.desc: Daily news and current-affairs programme offering discussion of breaking stories, exclusive interviews and audience interaction via social media.(n)

programme.title: Daily Politics
programme.desc: Parliamentary proceedings interspersed with discussions, interviews and reports from correspondents around the country. Presented by Jo Coburn.(n)

programme.title: Live International Bowls
programme.desc: The World Indoor Championships. Coverage of the World Pairs final at the Potters Leisure Resort in Hopton-on-Sea, Norfolk. Plus, coverage of the Open Singles first-round match between Alex Marshall and Gary Kelly, as Marshall begins his attempt to retain the title he won last year. Presented by Rishi Persad, with commentary by David Corkill.(n)

programme.title: Flog It
programme.desc: Will Axon and Elizabeth Talbot travel to Clacton-on-Sea in Essex, where they hunt for antiques and find valuables including a Victorian silver tea set and a small box made of a precious material. Presenter Paul Martin also explores the history of variety shows.(n)

programme.title: Eggheads
programme.desc: Jeremy Vine hosts the quiz in which the winners of famous game shows including Who Wants to Be a Millionaire? and Mastermind work as a team to tackle a new set of challengers hoping to win a cash prize.(n)

programme.title: Great British Railway Journeys
programme.desc: Michael Portillo sets out from Birmingham on the first leg of a trip to Dartmoor, and a visit to the city's town hall reveals a magnificent organ and the location for a celebrated music festival. Travelling south to Kidderminster, he works in a Royal Mail sorting office and discovers more about great postal innovator Rowland Hill, before he ending his journey in Worcester, where he learns about the origins of the British Medical Association.(n)

programme.title: Celebrity Antiques Road Trip
programme.desc: Actors and friends Philip Jackson and Brian Cox take on the antiques-hunting challenge. As Boomers star Philip and expert Phil Serrell go off-piste in their search, Hollywood A-lister Brian is joined by Paul Laidlaw, and together they are surprised to find one of the world's greatest works of art represented in the most unusual place.(n)

programme.title: University Challenge
programme.desc: In the first of the quarter-final matches, two teams of four students compete to make it to the next stage of the competition as they try to win two matches to progress to the semi-finals. Jeremy Paxman asks the questions.(n)

programme.title: Only Connect
programme.desc: Victoria Coren Mitchell asks the questions in the grand final of the quiz, as musicians the String Section take on either travel enthusiasts the Wayfarers or University of York students the Yorkers to succeed last year's winners the Orienteers and be named Only Connect series champions. The teams must use patience, lateral thinking and sheer inspiration to make connections between groups of four things that may at first appear not to be linked, with one set of clues consisting of Foke, Hombay, Egantic and Leakfast. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: Immortal Egypt with Joann Fletcher
programme.desc: Joann explores the peak of ancient Egyptian civilisation by looking at the Colossi of Memnon, two massive stone statues depicting Pharaoh Amenhotep III, and examining the lives of the workers and artisans involved in the building of the Valley of the Kings. programme.title: Wild Britain with Ray Mears
programme.desc: The survival expert explores the Peak District, one of the most popular places in the British countryside, where he spots short-eared owls hunting for voles and catches a glimpse of some of the red grouse and mountain hares that live among the heather of the Dark Peak. He also heads to the limestone uplands of the White Peak, whose rivers and streams are home to rare great-crested newts and caddis flies.(n)

programme.title: Wild Britain with Ray Mears
programme.desc: The survival expert explores Somerset's low-lying wetlands, one of the largest feeding grounds in Europe, where he spots little egret herons hunting for food and gathers reedmace pollen to make a pancake. He also catches a glimpse of an emperor dragonfly, and watches an otter gliding through water at dusk.(n)

programme.title: Wild Britain with Ray Mears
programme.desc: The survival expert visits a selection of Britain's hay meadows, uncovering vital links between them and some of the nation's most spectacular wildlife, including bees and butterflies that live among the diverse and colourful wild flowers, as well as green woodpeckers and barn owls. He also explains why more than 90 per cent of meadows have disappeared from the landscape since the end of the Second World War.(n)

programme.title: Operation Grand Canyon with Dan Snow
programme.desc: Part two of two. The historian and his team continue down the Colorado River in antique wooden boats as they re-create the pioneering 280-mile expedition through the Grand Canyon that was led by explorer John Wesley Powell in 1869. Along the way they carry out the same surveying tasks as the original party with period equipment, including taking photographs with a 19th-century 3D camera.(n)

programme.title: Harry's South Pole Heroes
programme.desc: Part two of two. Following their intensive training programme, Prince Harry and the soldiers embark on their expedition in the Antarctic as part of the Walking with the Wounded South Pole Allied Challenge 2013. Injured, frostbitten and nauseous from exhaustion and altitude, the teams are forced to abandon the race element and concentrate on survival as they battle through blizzards, biting winds and temperatures as low as -45 degrees Celsius. They are joined by two honorary members, Dominic West for Team Commonwealth, and Alexander Skarsgard for Team US.(n)

programme.title: The Story of Wales
programme.desc: Huw Edwards continues his exploration of the country's history by examining how, in 1485, Henry VII returned from exile in France to capture the English crown, becoming the first Welsh King of England. He discovers how the two countries became united under his leadership, leaving huge consequences for future generations, and explains the significance of being a landowner in the years that followed. The programme uses computer graphics and dramatic reconstructions to bring some of Wales' most historic moments to life.(n)

programme.title: Who Do You Think You Are

He discovers the first of his ancestors to settle on the island came from New York, so travels to America to further investigate his roots in Britain's colonial past.(n)

Plus, the hosts investigate why small-scale UK pig farmers are being left with huge amounts of meat they are unable to sell.(n)

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: Four hosts compete in the Midlands, kicks off with yoga-loving Daljit and his family Punjabi recipes, followed by fun-loving Nicola, who tries to encourage a festival vibe on her evening. Kirsty opts to showcase her Jamaican roots, although her food does not meet the approval of everyone, and David - who has kept everyone smiling all week - opts to do a bit of stand-up when he hosts. But who will walk away with the £1,000?.(n)

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: A week of dinner parties from Dudley in the West Midlands leads an aspiring Wag, a podium-dancing female plumber, a fan of self-grown food, and a hyper-critical guest into conflict. Amanda, Sophie, Ian and Khakan's evenings feature insults, psychic readings, the demonstration of surprising skills and burlesque entertainment as the four compete for the £1,000 cash prize.(n)

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: Swedish-American Judi Lembke hosts the first dinner party in London, hoping her relaxed attitude and an aperitif of schnapps will put the guests at ease and help her win the £1,000 cash prize. In an attempt to keep stress to a minimum, she prepares all the dishes in advance and plans to pass off shop-bought pastry as her own, unaware that some of her diners are self-proclaimed food snobs.(n)

programme.title: Phil Spencer: Secret Agent

programme.title: Phil Spencer: Secret Agent
programme.desc: The property expert helps Ken and Tricia Bolton to sell their house in St Leonards-on-Sea, East Sussex, which has struggled on the market for 18 months, despite its views of the English Channel. programme.title: Four in a Bed
programme.desc: The competition begins at Langsmeade House in Thame, Oxfordshire, where Dutch-born owner Marianne Abben and her housekeeper Fran Birchwood hope to demonstrate that their B&B offers the best value for money. The quirky pair's hosting style proves a hit with some of their guests, before others reveal their competitive side during a Charleston dance lesson.(n)

programme.title: Four in a Bed
programme.desc: The owners visit the Stratford House Guesthouse in Stratford-upon-Avon on their second outing, where couple Natasha and Dai Pollock hope to impress their peers. But things do not run smoothly, as the guests are left unimpressed with the decor and discover nasty surprises in some of the drawers.(n)

programme.title: Four in a Bed
programme.desc: The third B&B of the week is pet-friendly Edmund House in Deal, Kent, where owner Michael Prime is joined by his mum Lorna. On arrival, Marianne Abben and Fran Birchwood love the seaside-inspired room, but entrepreneur Mark Genders is far from thrilled by the `no frills' experience. Over dinner, tensions run high after self-confessed trouble-maker Marianne asks Mark to reveal which of the group he would and would not employ, and Lorna gets short shrift when she puts forward her application.(n)

programme.title: Four in a Bed
programme.desc: Entrepreneur Mark Genders welcomes the contestants to the Five Bells Pub in Berkshire and hopes they will approve of his small but perfectly formed rooms. He organises an ale-tasting activity, although it fails to please all of his guests. Michael and Lorna admit they have seen a new side of Mark - however, will it affect their feedback?.(n)

programme.title: Four in a Bed
programme.desc: The B&B owners settle some scores and discover how much they have been paid, before the winner is revealed. Marianne and Fran from Langsmead House begin by explaining that their worn rug is in fact a 200-year-old antique, Natasha and Dal from Stratford House confront Michael and Lorna about their strong language and cleaning techniques, while Mark Genders compares his experience at Edmund House to flying with a low budget airline.(n)

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: A week of dinner parties in Cardiff proves the participants have nothing in common as a businesswoman, a stay-at-home mum, a rugby fan and a theatre director compete for the £1,000 cash prize. Among the factors that put the quartet at one another's throats are a nude picture in a walk-in wardrobe, a mysterious incident in a hot-tub and a cameo appearance by a sporting star acting as a wine waiter.(n)

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: In Portsmouth, 55-year-old grandmother Maz is floored when car valet owner Chris tells her she looks older than her years. IT consultant and inventor Rob and Michael Jackson super-fan Sian jump to Maz's defence, but the damage is done. As the week progresses Maz gets her own back on Chris, and Rob rubs everyone up the wrong way with some traditional thinking after a teary conversation about whether real men cry. Amidst all the tears and tantrums, who will take home the £1,000 prize for throwing the perfect dinner party?.(n)

programme.title: Tricks of the Restaurant Trade
programme.desc: The team puts British pizzas to the test, comparing two very non-traditional pizzas from takeaway chain Papa John's with an authentic Italian pizza, and asking diners at an Italian restaurant which they prefer. Kate Quilton spends an afternoon having tea at The Ritz, which costs £50 a head, but when she takes over an east London cafe to recreate her own version of high tea, the ingredients cost less than £7 per person. Plus, Simon Rimmer commandeers a popular bistro in Manchester to demonstrate the common tricks of the trade that help restaurants make a profit.(n)

programme.title: Travel Man: 48 Hours in Paris
programme.desc: Richard Ayoade goes hurtling through a ruthlessly efficient mini-break in Paris with presenter and comedian Mel Giedroyc. Their base is a chic hotel famed for being the place where Oscar Wilde died, but there's no time to hang about soaking up the literary atmosphere, as they head to the Montparnasse Tower for arguably the best view of Paris, and one which has the bonus of including the Eiffel Tower. There's also calf's head casserole and snails, a scooter tour, `green fairy' absinthe, a Cordon Bleu cookery school, bespoke perfume and an art tour.(n)

programme.title: Walking the Himalayas

programme.title: In the Heart of the Sea
programme.desc: In the winter of 1820, the New England whaling ship Essex was assaulted by something no one could believe a whale of mammoth size and will, and an almost human sense of vengeance. The real-life maritime disaster would inspire Herman Melvilles Moby Dick. But that told only half the story. Heart of the Sea reveals the encounters harrowing aftermath, as the ships surviving crew is pushed to their limits and forced to do the unthinkable to stay alive. Braving storms, starvation, panic and despair, the men will call into question their deepest beliefs, from the value of their lives to the morality of their trade, as their captain searches for direction on the open sea and his first mate still seeks to bring the great whale down.(n)
